      Letter not found. Thetext given here is from the minutes of the Belfast(later Port Fairy)Municipal Councilmeetingof 16 May 1860, TheSuperintendent of thelocalBotanic Gardens, Henry Hedges, wrote on 2 May 1860 with advice on what plants to make application for to the Melbourne Botanic Garden. The Council probably then sent a request to M.

[Letter dated 15 May from Dr Müeller with case of shrubs &c for Botanical Gardens]



         Knight reportedM's letter at a Council meeting on 16 May 1860. On 12 June, Samuel Merrick wrote from Melbourne advising that he had sent a box of cuttings from M; these arrived by steamer on 13 June 1860. Then on 4 August 1860, Merrick advised that he had forwarded a case of Blue Gum seedlings from M (Minute book 2,BelfastMunicipal Council;
         Belfast gazette, 8June 1860, p. 2;
         Banner of Belfast, 19 May 1860, p. 3).
